commit.message: Fix bug in setting --no-search-header* from command line.

When set in the LESS environment variable, the parameter for
options --color, --quotes, --rscroll, --search-options and --intr
can be terminated with a space as well as with a dollar sign.
Doc and minor cleanup in Makefile.aut.

On systems that don't have nl_langinfo,
make default non-DOS charset utf-8 rather than latin1.
lesskey.nro.VER: Fix a minor markup issue

Fix erroneous parameter to usleep.
Was passing milliseconds, should pass microseconds.
Allow --rscroll to accept a non-ASCII character.

Make help file consistent in use of brackets around optional input.
If an option reports state when invoked with no parameter,
its parameter should be documented as optional.

Doc.
Improve description of MS-DOS-specific behavior of --color.
Change some attr variable names to cattr for consistency.

If we use spaces to move to the right column to print the rscroll
char, leave those spaces uncolored.
Previously they were colored with the rsrcoll color.

Fix bug viewing help file on Windows.
Code was calling filesize(-1) which just returns -1 on Linux
but crashes on Windows.

Fix bug with -D on command line.
Should not call init_win_colors before get_term is called.
